reviews.review: Confused, soulless, sloppy, silly and desperate.
Probably my favourite Star Wars movie of the last decade. Yes, its ridiculous in places and fanservicey as hell, but after the snorefest that was the LastJedi this movie was incrediby refreshing.
Perfect ending! I didn’t know what to expect, while still feeling the consistency and nostalgia of past episodes
I thought it was great! I just wish it was longer. The first 10 minutes felt very rushed. But i loved it.

Good way to round out the series. 3/4 of the way through, realizing how far off ‘Jedi’ was and how much work/time was needed to bring it back in focus - taking time, effort away from this installment story line and accelerating the pace.

This movie’s first act was very rushed and there were plot holes that weren’t explained. Those were my only complaints. I loved the acting in this movie, the visual effects in this movie were stunning as ever. The characters in this movie were very well written and more fleshed out. It was a very fun movie to watch and most importantly, I think it ended the Skywalker saga perfectly in a way that was satisfying.

a fantastic wrap up of the Skywalker saga. I will not give any spoilers away so I will not write a review other then to say it cleanly wraps up the movie an has a nice 2 to 3 minute ending that pays tribute sort of cue circle to the beginning of the franchise.

Just a retreat nothing new to see here. I was to me a better film than the last Jedi, but it suffered from trying to correct the errors of the previous film, I'm not concentrating too much on this one. Not the worst in the saga certainly far from the best.
Had an absolute blast watching this! Amazing visuals and a lot of feel good moments. I liked this movie better than the other 2 proceeding it.

A halfhearted stab at copying episode 6. Never expect more than utter mediocrity from Disney regarding Star Wars. I do not recommend paying good money to see episode 6 with worse characters and an even worse production crew putting together this terrible movie.
